result.execSummary:
The defendant Seth Dewain Washatko was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
AODA and follow through

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Defendant Seth Dewain Washatko in court with attorney Walter Arthur Piel.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15CT44 & 15CM177  @ 8:59 am. Court finds factual basis, accepts plea & finds def. Guilty to OWI 2nd in 15CT44, & Bailjumping in 15CM177. State gives sentencing recommendation. Atty Piel gives sentencing recommendation.  State replys to guidelines & would agree to probation on both cases. Court gives options. Atty Piel gives statement.  Court is comfortable with probation with treatment. Both parties agree with Judge.  Def. makes statement.  Court orders on
